social_posts.post_text:
Full #framily reunion yesterday celebrating our big brother @reggievanlee @reggievanlee_ , friend and mentor to so many, on his award from the @naacp Mid-Manhattan chapter at a waterside luncheon near the Throgs Neck Bridge! Who knew this bay in the Boogie Down Bronx where I was born was this gorgeous? #naacp

Congrats to his fellow awardees #blondellpinnock (pretty in pink), #alvinbragg (Manhattan DA, not pictured) and my @brownu classmate @dominick.boyce.73! Fun as always with fellow RVL birthday travel posse @msttunie @jehbk @stuart.archibald.54! Fall has fallen, but feels  like summer spirit ain’t QUITE over! 

Proud of these loyal community servants! #reggievanlee #dominickboyce #tamaratunie

Sunday Salute!Happiness is night out last night on @yvetteconcuatro block enjoying live gospel and gospel house from the @thesoapboxpresents final stoop sessions concert with perfect weather! What amazing vocals as always from @jhoardmusic and friends backed by a fabulous band. Thank you @msttunie @superbizzee @stuart.archibald.54 for the happy dances to Afrobeats after and dinner and great convo at @settepaninyc before. I love me a fun #harlemnights adventure with friends! #tamaratunie #soapboxpresents #kirkfranklin

TBT: flashback from a recent @kennedyadministration gig with @aliasboogie on bass! Happy birthday to the head-bopping fellow Jamerican Bronx-born bass player to the stars #alcarty. Always a pleasure being with him.

Grateful to Al for spending some of @mrjoness3 final hours with him in the hospital. Please get your tickets asap to the NYC musical tribute to #danieljones who loved this band tomorrow evening—presented by @sobsnyc and @chinahblac and hosted my @erro44 #ericroberson. 7 PM.

Trivia fact: Daniel and Al both played at my first record release concerts at #bbkings in 2003. Grateful for 20 years now as a recording artist and all the amazing musicians I’ve shared stages with like @kennedyadministration whose new album is out. Thank you Daniel for supporting us all with your joyful musical brilliance.

#gordonchambers #chinahblac #sobsnyc #livemusic 🇯🇲🎵🙏🏿

Join us tonight at @sobsnyc! Curated by @dwiskingbeef_official and @chinahblac, @erro44 will host, and myself and many others will play and sing our hearts out in remembrance of @mrjoness3 #danieljones. 7 pm. Wednesday , 204 Varick Street, NYC, Sept 20th❤️🙏🏿❤️🙏🏿 #ericroberson #gordonchambers #sobsnyc

Tonight’s the night! 7 pm! Thank you @sobsnyc for the venue, @erro44 for hosting, @chinahblac and @dwiskingbeef_official for curation and @mrjoness3 for all the love you gave and the lives you’ve touched. See y’all tonight NYC. #danieljones spirit lives on in this special #solvillage musical tribute! #sobsnyc #gordonchambers #ericroberson

Pics from last nights tribute to @mrjoness3 #danieljones at @sobsnyc. Words cannot describe the joy of this lovefest and musician family reunion! So great to celebrate him at this special #solvillage, the indie soul showcase he MD’d for many years with BFFs @jermaine_parrish on drums and @dwiskingbeef_official on keys and @erro44 as host with the most. Thank you so much @chinahblac for organizing this! Great to hear @carmenrodgers and @kennedyadministration croon on the mike-toss, 5x Grammy winner @robertglasper speak and bump into friends @catalystmusic @jermaine.hardsoul @hak.young Thank you Dallas, Houston, LA and Atlanta for flying into to show your love to his NYC family. More footage to follow. What a night! #sobsnyc #robertglasper #chinahblac #carmenrodgers

More scenes from Wednesday’s tribute to @mrjoness3 #danieljones at @sobsnyc. Tears from memories filled up in my eyes when I bumped into @ldtheproducer at rehearsal on Tuesday. Daniel and I gave teenage “Young David” his first professional gig years ago when twentysomething Daniel was my MD. It was a road trip to Massachusetts. 

In my time of brotherhood and mentoring Daniel, I lived long enough to see him grow as a mentor to other young musicians. To my beautiful surprise, I realized I had met the Baltimore-born members of the Philly-based band @its_treway a month before at an @bmoreepicfam showcase. They played the show and turned it out. Also on the bill was the amazing songstress @theestout who crooned an emotional and futuristic “A Song For You.”

Thank you again @chinahblac for curating the evening with @dwiskingbeef_official AND closing the show singing songs you wrote with @mrjoness3. You looked and sounded like a funk goddess! Brava, congrats and thank you for organizing!

#stout #chinahblac #treway #asongforyou

My first time singing “‘Missing You” from “Set It Off” (which I covered on my Sincere album) with a live band. Wrote this after my grandmother passed in the 90s. Never imagined I’d sing it for so many young loved ones as the years went by. Thank you @dwiskingbeef_official @jermaine_parrish for encouraging me to take my time and sing the whole song and not just a snippet. #missingyou #barryeastmond #setitoffmovie 

Rest in Peace @mrjoness3 #danieljones our hero with a heart open wide, born on the same day as my other heavenly younger brother #kilvinjohnsonjunior. See you on the other side when my time comes. “Who would have known that you’ve have to go/so suddenly so fast.” I wore a tee-shirt from Daniel’s fashion line. What a visionary and entrepreneur he was! Thank you again @sobsnyc and @chinahblac❤️ #gordonchambers #brandynorwood #chakakhan #gladysknight #tamia

Sunday Inspiration: Also sang “Lead Me” from my Sincere album at the @sobsnyc tribute to @mrjoness3 #danieljones last Wednesday. We had a little church in the jook joint. Thank you @dwiskingbeef_official for always putting together a great band when we play, and what a beautiful guitar solo from @waltwizard. #gordonchambers 

Wrote this song with Daniel’s great guitarist friend Mike Severson. He knew all the finest musicians and introduced many of us to each other. God is still in control through whatever you’re going through. Let him use you and lead you. Happy Sunday from NYC.

Big thanks to my mega talented buddy @leslieodomjr for arranging house seats yesterday for his return to broadway show @purliebway #purlievictorious, written by #ossiedavis who costarred in it with wife #rubydee. This Tony and Grammy winner and Oscar nominee and entire cast are excellent in this dark comedy about white supremacy. Run to the @musicboxtheatre to see this y’all! #leslieodumjr

Happy heavenly 87th birthday to the late great @winniemandela__ #winniemandela who kindly received myself and @fridayarts to her home 9 years ago for both a private meeting and her 78th birthday party weeks later where I shared a poem I wrote in her honor.

Forever grateful for her beloved granddaughter @zolekamandela for setting everything up for us. Condolences to her husband and six children on her transition yesterday at 43 after years of courageously fighting breast cancer and burying her 13-year-old daughter years ago killed in a car accident. Her mother Zindzi awaits her above who passed away in 2020. 

Peace and blessing to this family and to the country of #southafrica that I love so much. The kindest warmest people ever. Amandla. 🇿🇦 #zolekamandela #mandelafamily

TBT: sooo grateful for this beautiful intro that moved me to tears before I sang at last weeks @sobsnyc tribute to @mrjoness3 hosted by King of Indie Soul and Kindness my friend and fellow Libra singer-songwriter @erro44 #ericroberson! HBD to this humble legend to turned 50 years young yesterday!!

Thank you for paving the way for independent artists and always being loving and honorable to all! He plays @sonyhall on October 5th to celebrate 50 years of a beautiful life of music, family and friendship! We’ll never forget you #danieljones ❤️❤️ #gordonchambers #sobsnyc #sonyhall #fiftiethbirthday #solvillage

Had a blast In Wednesday seeing the the new Broadway play #jajasafricanhairbraiding by @jjbioh #jocelynbioh at @mtc_nyc starring @dominiquethorne (aka Ironheart “Wakanda Forever” “Judas The Black Messiah”)! Great to support friends @iammetch and Grammy-nominated jazz singer @somimusic in their Broadway debuts in this immigrant American dream dramatic comedy. Bumped into friend @denisebinspired who loves the arts like I do! NYC go and see this brilliant work by this Ghanaian-American actress-playwright. The #manhattantheatreclub never misses. I love NYC! #dominquethorne #theatre

Happy 90th birthday today to @cissyhouston_! Thank you for all you’ve done for music! Soul survivor, gospel legend, Atlantic Records pop royalty and Queen Mother to @whitneyhouston! New Hope Baptist of Newark finest! And thank you @jmlegrairstudio —master teacher like #cissyhouston-for spreading the joy of vocal #blackexcellence !

A beautiful afternoon it was celebrating matriarch @cissyhouston_ #90thbirthday with @mpathouston @garymhouston @donnakhouston @rayahhouston and more family and close friends. Grateful for wonderful memories with this clan who has always welcomed like a brother. I’m amazed at all this legend has done for music: from the Drinkard Singers, Sweet Inspirations, Aretha, Elvis, Chaka, Luther, the New Hope Baptist Church to Whitney Houston, her sound has made an imprint on thousands of recordings. @whitneyhouston and I would talk about her catalogue for hours and hours at a time. View her PBS documentary “Sweet Inspiration” on YouTube and read her two memoirs and be amazed at her strength, courage, wisdom and transparency. #cissyhouston #pathouston #newarknj #whitneyhouston

Happy heavenly 78th birthday #donnyhathaway. Sang this at home spontaneously for my friend @iamkenpen in 2021. We thank your late father who passed this year for the great man he molded in you. The story of the song lyric is so poignant. Please learn more about and support the mental health initiatives @donnyhathawaylp is undertaking. May we all, through all we are going through, be free. Thank you @donnitacamille who shares my birthday for your passion for community emotional well-being. #libraseason #gordonchambers

Cannot wait for this film! Amazing and generous of @beyonce to make a film for those who missed the incredible tour I’m mad I didn’t see a second time, to teach us about the discipline of her process. Thank you @jennydeluxe for your INCREDIBLE @nytimes article about Queen B and @kevinpowellinbrooklyn for posting a clip of it. She makes us SO damn proud! #beyonce #jennawortham

Two double bullseyes ain’t shabby for my first time at this! Gotta work on my aim for the rematch. I love friends who bring the fun in new ways I would never venture into on my own. Scenes from a weekend visit to @hatchetsandhops in #williamsburg! Thank you hermano @esmaylin18! What fun! #libraseason Birthday countdown. #hatchesandhops

Bonding. Brotherhood. Excavation. Deeper Inhalation. Vocal Exploration. A beautiful lesson #1 with @shanemaux ! A friend of @iamsteffreed is a friend of mine! Thank you for your transparency and willingness to let your soul sing! The journey has begun. The joy of #vocalcoaching always fills my soul #artistdevelopment #gordonchambers #lifelessons

TBT: I’ll never forget the day I met singer-turned-designer Wayne Williams at a recording session for a British boyband I wrote for in the late 90s called #anotherlevel. He asked me a million questions that day and soon thereafter kept in touch and immediately started calling me “Uncle G.” The joy and honor of mentorship. When the quartet disbanded he moved to Brooklyn and started a fashion line called @brklnbloke that sold mostly in the #williamsburg streets. That brands slow and steady buzz and build graduated him to owning his own brick and mortar store inside @grandcentralnyc #grandcentralterminal. 

Dreams come true when you do the work! Congrats nephew #waynewilliams. You’ve truly gone to another level, literally. So proud of you. Please stop by and support this happy man of action, intention and industry transformation. #brklnbloke #blackbritish

Flashback Friday: friendship reunion with Grammy-nominated Chicago #housemusic legend @stevesilkhurley last week at @sohohouse #dumbo. An honor to co-write and sing on this 2002 inspirational single for him. Looking amazing at 60 and spinning all over the world and spreading joy! #stevesilkhurley #gordonchambers #chicagohousemusic #dontgiveup #chicagosfinest

Also at @stevesilkhurley party weeks ago was legendary DJ and record exec @djmerlinbobb! Worked closely with this humble giant and @iamsylviarhone and their team on many of my hits for Anita Baker, Yolanda Adams, Gerald Levert—as well as soundtracks for Madeas Family Reunion and Set It Off (thanks @inductbrandy for the shoutout about #missingyou). Great to see his son @vaughnbobbwillesq who’s all grown up an new an entertainment lawyer in NYC. Met him as a teenager. Time flies! Like father, like son. So proud of you! #merlinbobb #atlanticrecords #eastwestrecords #ludlowhouse #sohohouse

During birthday countdown I love to run the streets and hear fabulous music! Thank you @apollotheater and #apollomusiccafe for the sights and sounds of @iamalicaldwell and @kamasiwashington! @iamsteffreed and @superbizzee and @yvetteconcuatro and I had a ball! Thank you so much @darius_booker_nyc and DJ for the impromptu spontaneous serenade next door at the new bar at the Victoria Hotel! Thank you @kamilahf  and @leatrice313 for arranging our seating! So proud of the team at the #apollotheater. The Intersection continues today, curated in collaboration with @tanehisicoates! Come and listen and learn! #alicaldwell #kamasiwashington . Happy Sunday all! #pattilabelle #ifonlyyouknew

Scenes and snippets at the ideas joyfest from my weekend uptown at the @apollotheater for #theintersection (a curatorial collab with author #tanehisicoates). Thank you @kerrywashington @domorisseau @nikolehannahjones for your brilliance! Thank you @the_yolanda_wyns_experience @iamsteffreed and @superbizzee for your birthday countdown serenades at @sugarbarnyc and @roosterharlem. What fun! Congrats @kamilahf @leatrice313 and the whole #apollotheater staff on an intellectual and inspirational joyride of #blackexcellence! #kerrywashington

Happy 79th birthday to one of my favorite singer-songwriters of all time! Visionary, fashionista, BadAss, Afro-Futurist #labelle Icon @nonahendryx. What an honor to have shared stages with this fellow Libra  via @carlhancockrux and #blackrockcoalition! #nonahendryx #linconcenterfestival #pattilabelle #sarahdash #pattilabelleandthebluebelles

TBT: My 54th has come! Happy birthday to me. This pic was taken at my 50th at @goldbarnewyork. Thank you Aunt Joy for sending it to me! Sending greetings as we speak from beautiful #puglia Italy (one of my favorite countries in the world). Always so grateful to see coveted corners of the world. More pics from here to come. God continues to bless me infinitely and I will forever praise Him. #gordonchambers #fiftyfourthbirthday #goldbarnyc #tootsandthemaytals

Thank you ALL for hundreds and hundreds of beautiful texts, FaceTimes, phone calls, posts, video tributes from friends, throwback family pics and videos. Studio 54 has come. Living La dolce vita❤️❤️Sending you love, health and strength from sunny #puglia! Scenes from yesterdays sail boat ride in the Adriatic Sea. How sweet it is to be so loved by all of you! God bless❤️🙏🏿❤️ May we all bring joy and peace to this crazy world we live in by spreading love! #gordonchambers #fiftyfourthbirthday

Celebrating my big brother @m.sabir_ward #sixtiethbirthday tonight with his posse of 12 in beautiful #puglia #italy—the Southern boot of my favorite European country where 60 million olive trees abound, scrumptious food is served and taught in cooking classes and traveling friends make memories in lands where buildings have stood tall for thousands of years! Grateful for my fellow #libra friend who always sets a stylish tone for folks to gather in peace, fairness and beauty. Thanks for a beautiful friendship to us all filled with unconditional love galore! Thank you @masseriaauraterrae for hosting us! And bravo to #larrysatterfield for planning so exquisitely! #friendship

Scenes for #puglia! #trulli ancient rooftops, olive gardens, homemade focaccia, scenic Adriatic seasides make for fun impromptu photo shoots! Thank you @everybodyblack23 for snapping me  jumping for joy and stopping to admire the beauty—honoring the #libra in me. I love me some Italy! Thank you @sidrasmithofficial and @stanleytucci for the inspiration to come here! #blackswhotravel #alberobello #searchingforitaly #jumpforjoy

Scenes from scenic and deeply historic #matera in #puglia where the James Bond film #notimetodie was filmed. So fascinating how cities have been built on these rock formations and caves for thousands of years. It now houses many Airbnbs, stylish hotels and #unesco-interested tourists. Our tour guide who is an archeologist said this place reminds us how “fluid time and space” really are. A great day out chatting with @doreenchambersinteriors and a dinner thereafter in the sexy streets of #bari with  @jehbk

Sunday Inspiration! When traveling I like to get up early and walk and give God thanks for my life, limbs and liberty especially when so many freedoms are being taken away around the world by injustice and war. To see the world is the greatest blessing, opens perspective and has you reflect. This part of Italy called #puglia is unpretentious, earthy and souful—like this wonderful smiling farmer I chatted with. Neither of spoke the other’s language, but we feel the energy of shared passion for health and spreading love and joy: just because. ❤️🙏🏿❤️🙏🏿

Thanks sis! Happy Sunday❤️❤️ Love you mama. What a joyful journey.

・・・
@gordonchambers HAPPY BELATED BIRTHDAY.  I love you and I’m so blessed to have you in my life. Keep smilin', keep shinin', knowing you can always count on me, for sure, cause that’s what friends are for. 🎂♥️🎉

Some lunch spreads you’ll NEVER forget! Scenes from yesterday’s home cooked feast before a wine tasting at @terredisanvito vineyard estates—a family-owned business that hosted us like visiting cousins. In #italy, food is love. In #puglia much of the wheat, tomatoes and olives are grown that feed the nation. At #terredisanvito the Malbec is world-renowned. A very eat, drink and be merry Happy Sunday it surely was! Perfect setting to make memories. A friend of @m.sabir_ward is a friend of mine. Thank you my fellow #libraseason brother for gathering us. #winetasting #blackswhotravel

#libraseason rules my family on both sides! Welcome to the amazing fifties @jellmd. Cousins are your first friends. So proud of the son, big brother, father, uncle, doctor and community leader you’ve grown into! God bless! #fiftiethbirthday #cousinlove

This is the first time ever in my life that I’ve taken a trip for my birthday. Thank you @m.sabir_ward who turned 60 the day after I turned 54 for having me share the celebration and make beautiful memories in #puglia #italy. The hospitality here reminds me of my homeland Jamaica—and island that also believes in the grand breakfast spread! Truly grateful to Elisa from @southernvisionstravel for planning such a wonderful La dolce vita experienza! Gratzi to the hotel owners and staffs, drivers, tour guides, restaurants and all our hosts at all our stops (including this olive grove) for treatment par excellence! All aboard. Heading home—belly full and heart happy. I love ITALY. I’ll be back—again and again.

Flashback Friday: Back in NYC, but my heart is still in #puglia where I brought in the year I’m calling Studio 54 with friends of @m.sabir_ward! What joy we shared exploring our final cities #bari and #lecce, wining, dining and taking a cooking class with neighbors @doreenchambersinteriors and foodie hubby Phillipe and many more. Got the sad and sudden news that yet another dear beloved friend of almost 30
year mixed/media artist, painter and professor @radcliffebaileyjr #radcliffebailey has joined the ancestors today. What beautiful memories I have with this Atlanta gentleman whose work I began collecting when we befriended during my @essence years when I covered him as arts-entertainment editor. 

Bailey was warm, soulful, talked in parables, loved a foodie meal and strong cocktail, always generous having friends visit his studio home that sprawled in the woods. He played jazz while he painted and was so proud of his kids. To know him was truly to love him. I’m truly grateful to all that took care of him in his battle with cancer. He loved music deeply. Jersey-born but Atlanta’s  finest, African spirit rooted on Southern land now high in the heavenly clouds. 

Thank you RC for the love you gave to me, to your friends and family, to your canvases that will never die. #friendship #blackart #jackshainmangallery #atlanta

Flashback Friday: I have a special place in my heart for families that lose a loved one in the holiday seasons. My maternal grandmother Merle Sylvia Ellis ascended in Kingston thirty years ago today. Growing up as the first grandchild in the family, it was always an honor to play my heart out for her at recitals and show her my new songs when she visited. I knew she and Grandpa had had high expectations. 

Trivia fact: I channeled my mother’s grief into the lyrics of “Missing You.” I know this singing seamstress from Jamaica smiles down as her family continues to gather and stay strong five generations later. Rest in Power and thank you for teaching all how to lead with love. Happy Holidays all. May your memories soothe your souls. #missingyou #grandmotherslove #setitoffsoundtrack #brandy #gordonchambers

Please help me wish the happiest of birthday wishes to Valerie DeRuth Ellis Chambers of Port Antonio, Kingston, The Bronx, Navarre and Teaneck. Grateful God has given us 79 years of life today for this amazing unconditionally loving mother, wife, grandmother, great-grandmother, sister, aunt, grandaunt, caretaker and friend to so many. To quote Patti LaBelle “it’s a joy to have your love.” Thank you for how much you care. May you stay #foreveryoung ❤️❤️

Mommy thanks you ALL for her abundant birthday well wishes yesterday. The Sagittarius party continues because my Dad Byron George Chambers (nicknamed “Bala” in his Montego Bay childhood) turns 80 years young today! 

When I think of Daddy, I smile wide. Mommy always told me as a child, “I’m your best friend, but you are your father’s child.” This man truly knows how to enjoy LIFE! He eats plentifully, laughs loud, gets up to do what must be done and keeps an optimistic spirit about every day God has made. Not only a loyal husband and loving father to Brian and I, Daddy is amazing grandfather. Uncle B” who would pack the car with kids to go to the ski slopes, Great Advenuture, family vacation or a roller skaking rink. All the parents trusted him and all the kids came to our house to play Atari, rehearse, break dance, try Jamaican foods and have a ball in the basement. 

Daddy was a beloved car salesman who started an Allstate franchise for 37 years in the Bronx. Being of service with dignity, integrity for the community, and mentoring other men (especially fellow immigrant cricket players) was the essence of him. It often took time away from our household but set a tone for how I would walk in the world. Daddy supported me with music lessons, encouraging me to sing and allowing me to attend the college @brownu I felt would honor my artistic spirit and came to EVERY local concert.

Cheers to an amazing man who garners ‘nuff respect! @gwendolynquinnofficial always said my parents were the music industry parents. When people would tell me “I know your parents are proud of you, my answer has always been and will always be I am proud of them!”

Salute Daddy! Keep smiling, shining, singing and dancing. We love you! Happy #80thbirthday

Thank you @officiallybyronwalker for posting this clip on living legend #anitabaker in Dallas. This song reminds us to say sorry when needed. A lesson and a blessing that always the humbles the soul. “When the road (pun intended) gets rough we say things we should not say” God bless the Queen of the Quiet Storm—still in vintage voice—who changed my life and has brought us four decades of beautiful music. #iapologize #gordonchambers #timelessmusic

Mom and Dad send glorious thank you to all of you for their 79th and 80th birthday wishes! Scenes from our little dinner at home on Tuesday. “When I think of home I think of a place, where there is love overflowing.” Happy holidays all! Sending strength to any families who’ve lost a loved one in 2023. May the memories warm your hearts. #thechambersfamily #saggitariusseason♐️

TBT: Thank you @bobbyxwhitney and @jpsalmz for your posts this week highlighting my songs on “Just Whitney” and “One Wish: The Holiday Album”. This “My Love” recording session was featured in the “Whitney” documentary. She was the loving big sister to #bobbybrown and I that day, ensuring that her husbands vocals came out great. He was nervous and hadn’t recorded in years but delivered beautifully. Both of these albums were released in #saggitariusseason. I also was in a holiday episode of “Being Bobby Brown.” 

Holidays remind you often of loved ones who have joined the ancestors. Will love you forever @whitneyhouston. Thanks for the memories and joy your music continues to bring the world-especially ar Christmas. #gordonchambers #holidaymusic #bobbyandwhitney #mylove #onewish

Countdown to the Grammys! She is nominated for Best African Performance (new category) and “Water” just hit #1 on the Rhythmic Crossover Category! social_posts.post_text: The music video I made in my temporary apartment (while my house was in post-fire renovation) from family pictures that I released on Christmas Day 2017 for my song “Circle of Love” from my Surrender album. Please add this to your holiday playlists and enjoy your gatherings today and memories! Merry Christmas and happy holidays all! #gordonchambers #circleoflove #holidaymusic

One of my favorite lines in the movie “A Raisin In The Sun” is said between Mama Lena Younger and daughter Beneatha. “In my mother’s house, there is STILL God.” Thank you Mommy and Daddy for hosting and Aunt Joan @mrspeterjoan for cooking and supporting us all as always as a family. We cherish you. Through a 2023 of trials, tribulations and heavenly transitions, we came together in celebration of what God has done on Earth and continues to do. 

A wonderful Christmas we had and we wished cousin @sheldonnoel06 @sheldonwoodley a happy 50th birthday! Happy Boxing Day (a Caribbean holiday) and Happy Kwaanza all! Today is UMOJA: unity for the family and community. Can I get a witness? #holidaygathering #jamaicanfamily #raisininthesun 🇯🇲

Thanks for the lipsync shoutout @rythemzroye_ from Morroco of a song I co-wrote and was featured on for @angelajohnsonmusic producer album! Thanks for the soundtrack shoutout to celebrate your Moms 80th birthday @rondezvous01. Always honored to learn what my songs mean to other people—especially when music lovers dig deep into my indie catalog. Grateful! Happy Kwaanza. Today is #kujichagulia day which celebrates #selfdetermination. Being an indie requires that. Shoutout to all my peeps who release their music themselves and all who support us! #gordonchambers #circleoflove #angelajohnson

Scenes from December first #vocalcoaching lessons with @ajthegent, @mdm.negritabonita and friend Mariah and  @milanparodie who came inspired by @tyla and found her “halo”. Today is #ujima. Helping singers find their voices is so uplifting for me! Thank you all for your trust! #gordonchambers #artistdevelopment

Today is the #nia day of #kwaanza, and Nia means purpose. It has always been my honor to present in NYC public schools. @simonebailey14 invited me to @p79mhoran recently to share my journey with her special education students. Coretta was beaming with enthusiasm. The joy of #vocalcoaching and #musiceducation honors all the mentors and  instructors that poured into me during my high school years. I love helping people of all ages find their purpose through the arts and self-expression 

Trivia fact: I was accepted by @teachforamerica to teach in NYC  in 1990 after graduation but went to @essence instead. #gordonchambers #nycschools

Reflection: 2023 tested me. I won’t lie. I buried many loved ones. I sang for several unexpected funerals, spoke at several memorials and wrote many remembrance poems. I stayed strong for many loved ones and kept a happy face up but “it was inside that I cried” (to quote Cece Penniston). Thanks to all who listened unselfishly for hours through all it all with no judgement and prayed for me. I love you “more than you’ll ever know” (Donny Hathaway)🎵❤️

But I also traveled a great deal, taught and inspired many, supported my friends and family through changes, trials and tribulations. It was a year of grief and gratitude, but I believe I made a difference.
God is STILL good, and I am thankful for all the lessons and stewardship of my life. Come on 2024. I’m ready for whatever you bring me. And I won’t complain. Can I get a witness? Happy New Years all. Keep the faith! ❤️🙏🏿

#auldlangsyne #imani #happynewyear #2024 ! From my heart to yours! Let’s keep the faith for what only the Most High can do. Thank you @the_yolanda_wyns_experience for sending! Thank you @thegroupfire for Black make brotherhood and vocal excellence here! #thegroupfire

So excited for what God is doing through this 21-year-old Grammy-nominated #africanpopstar from #johanessburg #southafrica! Album drops in March. 

So proud of her work ethic and team! Shoutout to her management @brandonvhixon @tirinda @khufu of @wemakemusicnyc and @completemusicstudios for hosting our rehearsals. Happy New Year all! ! #tyla #ryanseacrest #gordonchambers #wemakemusic #vocalcoaching #vocalcoach #artistdevelopment

I enjoyed sharing with them about what #miriammakeba #patapata meant to my Jamaican family growing up at dance parties in our basement. It was the first song fro’ #southafrica to ever win a Grammy! The Grammy-nominated “Water” has the whole world singing and dancing to a New South African joyful jam! #gordonchambere #tyla #vocalcoaching #artistdevelopment #completemusicstudios

Appreciation Post: finally got to take my Mom to see @thecolorpurple yesterday. Felt proud to see the credits roll and see Oprah And Whoopi’s name as producers of this version: giving back to the story that changed their lives. Don’t go (if you haven’t as yet) to compare this version to the last. Go to reexperience #alicewalker timeless story of self-discovery, triumph, redemption and forgiveness from wherever you are in your life NOW and bring your tissues. You’ll be moved! Trust. #thecolorpurple 

I also personally went to hear the exquisitely crafted songs crafted by cowriter @brendarussellmusic (“Piano In the Dark” “Get Here” “Le Restaurant” “If Only For One Night”) once again. This end title song has also uplifted me when my spirit is low: reminding to “look what God has (already) done” Brenda’s pen is one of my favorites of all time. #brendarussell 

Congrats to the entire cast including a few I’ve met @coreyhawkins and friends @jonbatiste and @aunjanue_ellis447. And last and NOT least, shoutout to friends and I saw on the Broadway stage 10x like @the_yolanda_wyns_experience (“Church Lady/Sofia”) @iamelisabethwithers (“Shug” who’ve I’ve written many songs for) and @jenniferhollidaydreamgirl (“Shug”) who lovingly gifted me seats to the final performance ever where she costarred with @cynthiaerivo (“Celie”). I’ll never forget @lamont.gordon1 and I sitting next to @hillaryclinton and watching the song heal her soul weeks after the 2016 election. #hilaryclinton 

What a show! What a film! What a story! May it be told again and again for new generations to learn from it. I love it “like a blade of corn, like a honeybee,like a waterfall, all apart of me”❤️🙏🏿❤️🙏🏿❤️🙏🏿🎵🎵🎵💪💪

Congrats to living legend #danaowens and also to #theclarksisters who will be honored at the Grammys this year for lifetime achievement! Grateful! RIP Lancelot and Rita Owens

#gordonchambers #kennedycenterawards #karenclarksheard #twinkieclark #deniseclarkbradford

TBT: the most amazing unexpected belated surprise gift came personally delivered last week to my doorstep by my long-time sis @yvetteconcuatro and her executive director @deegraceg of @readalliance! I’m still in shock! They commissioned Jamaican oil painter @alphanso_artist (a friend of office manger Victoria Mitchell) to paint the first time I came as a guest speaker to this organizations youth conference. 

#readalliance hires NYC teenagers to tutor elementary school kids to read. If I hadn’t fallen in love with words as a child, my adulthood would have looked very different. Please to the website and learn more about this incredible organization that I love so much! 

Their spring 2024 gala will be held in NYC on May 14th. Tickets available now and donations accepted all year round. How great it is to grow up and support your friends causes. Love you love you @yvetteconcuatro, Chief Strategy Officer. Keep being a light for the youth of our city. #wearetheworldwearethechildren #alphansoblake #gordonchambers #youthorganization

I LOOOVE a great music documentary! Clips from one I discovered on great drummer-composer @maxroachfilm #maxroach that I discovered on #pbs! He married and mentored the late GREAT and unsung actress and jazz singer #abbeylincoln to tell her own stories as a songwriter. 

Their union was one of high Afrocentric art and activism. She mentored me right out of college and told me “you’ll never really be an artist unless you’re writing.” These clips of @_abbeylincon_ @abbey_lincoln_film @ brought back beautiful memories of times spent in her Harlem apt in the early 90s. Her song “Throw It Away” moves me like no other.

Happy heavenly birthday to Max Roach who would have been 100 yesterday. Geniuses they were. RIP Abbey (aka #aminatamoseka and Gabby Woolridge) , a woman of constant reincarnation and boundless creativity. May her full story one day also be told. #soniasanchez #questlove #freedomnowsuite #artandactivism
Gordon Chambers is one of R&B's greatest gems. What's your favorite song written by @gordonchambers?

Whew y’all! Words cannot express my appreciation for the beautiful commentary on my catalogue on @youknowigotsoul post about my hits last week Thursday. It came during a week I needed uplifting. Took me days to fully take in all the gratitude.

As a songwriter the songs that come deep from your heart touch you just as deeply as those that hit the charts. On my Love Stories and Surrender albums I covered “If It Wasn’t For Your Love” (recorded first by @heatherheadley) which I wrote as a thank you to my parents and “One Voice” (recorded by @brandy) written about what music means to me as a conduit of healing for the world. #ifitwasntforyourlove #onevoice 

Both these songs—often performed at weddings and choir competitions—reference “the dream” #mlk lived and died for that so that a little black boy like me could grow up in the first town to voluntarily desegregate its public schools— #teanecknj—to pursue my dreams. 
God has been so good to me. Happy #mlkday to all your music lovers and freedom fighters! #gordonchambers 

“I have decided to stick with love/ Hate is to great a burden to bear”—#martinlutherkingquotes #brandy #heatherheadley #essenceawards

Couldn’t make his funeral but felt so good to sit in the room DJ Funmi booked and hear @ekepnkwelle croon at @dizzysjazzclub. Thank you @sunnyjazzdc for inviting me. In jazz the good sometimes the good (like he and my friend @groveydean #royhargrove) often die young. 

When she sang #abbeylincoln #cagedbird tears rolled down my eyes remembering how kind Abbey and Roy were to me in my early years finding my groove in this city. Funmi was similarly warm and always so hospitable to me at #dizzyjazzclub in later years. Rest in power brother. And thank you for your incredible warmth, laughter and loving spirit to so very many. #jazz #jazzatlincolncenter #funmiononaiye #ekepnkwelle

Great to hear three of @luthervandross former background singers @l.i.s.a.f.i.s.c.h.e.r @cindymizelle (my hometown childhood friend) and @patricia.lacy1218 (also a @thesoundsofblackness alum) take leads last night as featured guests with @louievega 10-piece orchestra at the @bluenotenyc. It was a Latin Soul Extravaganza with legend @auwee730 on BGs and my boo @dawntallman tagging on their signature hit “I am The Black Gold Of The Sun”. #audreywheeler #dawntallman 

Saw #littlelouievega in #ibiza last summer. Humble house music legend and DJ extraordinaire. Thank you @kacyduke. What fun! #cindymizelle #lisafischer! Can NOT wait to see the #luthervandross documentary.

What a pleasure to finally meet the 2x #grammywinner @samarajoysings tonight after her set at the @bluenotenyc. What a lady she is—-classy, graceful and kind in her energy—and so supportive of her bandmates who also write and arrange music for her! #samarajoy also sang some gorgeous tunes she penned! What a star shining bright for the culture!

@samarajoysings is often compared to @sarah_vaughan_fanpage tonally, but her dexterity, songwriting skills and fast-paced swing would make ancestor Auntie #bettycarter proud! This breakneck-tempo rendition of Betty’s classic “Tight” blew me away. Go ‘head on daughter of soul and gospel and the future of jazz! Yes #samarajoy. Hold on, TIGHT!! Your career is about to skyrocket for a lifetime journey. Thank you @bluenotenyc for booking her again in this room for the up-and-close sold-out experience and for my front-row seat to experience this 24-year-old wunderkind. #jazzvocal #bluenotejazzclub #tight

Had to post yet one more clip! It’s the flip into fearless soprano territory from her smoky alto into the last verse of #nancywilson #guesswhoisawtoday and the segue into the bridge of @steviewonderlegacy #lately that ALSO took me OUT during the encore of @samarajoysings second set. This moment sent me into a gospel-soul-jazz frenzy! Every musical sense in my body shivered. This #younggiftedandblack chanteuse commands her craft and shows such respect for the songbooks that have inspired her. Just amazingly inspirational. Thank you @bluenotenyc ! #samarajoy #bluenotenewyork

The Queen has left the building. RIP #marlenashaw, the comedic jazz diva known for this gem and the often-sampled “California Soul” And “Woman of the Ghetto” . Thank you for 81 years of inimitable phrasing. #goawaylittleboy . One of of my favorite live albums of all time!
